<abstract><t>This memo specifies LISP-SEC, a set of security mechanisms that provide origin authentication, integrity and anti-replay protection to LISP's EID-to-RLOC mapping data conveyed via mapping lookup process.  LISP-SEC also enables verification of authorization on EID- prefix claims in Map-Reply messages.</t></abstract>

